stylometry: Decision trees are important because they allow us to make trees that have various outcomes that are possible and tell us the probability that they will happen.  They also give us a solid YES or NO answer which tells us whether to make that decision or not.  They are used by listing all possible options and giving significant information so that the options can be weighed and a useful solution can be set.  A decision tree can be used to help a bank whether to give a client a loan.  Based off of past loans, records, and any information that can be used about them, a decision tree can see whether giving them a loan is a very low risk that should be capitalized on, or extrmely high one that should not be taken.
